ly","Stocks, Ellesmere, Shropshire, England":"Ellesmere, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","of,Uwch Caeach cmt,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Meisgyn,Penychen,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Dutch: occupational name for a cobbler.","Slovenian: nickname for a talkative person, from <i>lapati</i> ‘to babble’, or a topographic name from dialect <i>lap</i> ‘abyss’. Compare   Lapp   4."],"variants":[{"name":"Lapp","meanings":["German, English, and Dutch: from Middle High German and Middle English <i>lappe</i>, Middle Dutch <i>lap</i> ‘cloth, patch, rag’, a metonymic occupational name for a mender of clothes or shoes, or a nickname given to someone who wore ragged clothes or garments with loose folds, flaps, or hanging sleeves, or who had fleshy folds of skin on his face, neck, or body.","German: nickname for a simple-minded person, from Middle Low German <i>lappe</i> ‘fool’. This surname (in any of the two possible senses; see also 1 above) is also found in France (mainly Alsace, also Lorraine).","English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>lappe</i> ‘burdock’, perhaps for someone with a prickly character."]}]},{"name":"Gruffydd","type":"LAST","meanings":["Welsh: The Welsh name; from creffydd, strong faith, or strong in faith. Gruffydd, a Welsh form of Gryffydd."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewelyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llywelyn ap Gruffydd was born in 1303, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Gruffydd Llwyd ap Llywelyn Later made Lord of Gellingham, was 47 and his mother, Tangwystl ferch leuaf ab Mareddydd ap Madog of Bodiudris, was 21. He married Margred Verch Madog Fychan about 1328, in Ellesmere, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1340, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1303–1340":"1303–1340","1294–Female":"1294–Surnud","1303–Female":"1303–Surnud","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1332–1357":"1332–1357","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","1257–Male":"1257–Surnud","1283–Female":"1283–Surnud","1303":"1303","1357":"1357","1257":"1257","1334":"1334","ABT    1330":"umbes 1330","1332":"1332","about 1334":"umbes 1334","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1283":"1283","1294":"1294","Abt 1328":"umbes 1328","Bryncunallt, Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Meisayn, Penyc, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","{Lln ap Gwrgan}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Stocks, Ellesmere, Shropshire, England":"Ellesmere, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of,Uwch Caeach cmt,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Meisgyn,Penychen,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1303–1340":"1303–1340","1294–Female":"1294–Kuollut","1303–Female":"1303–Kuollut","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1332–1357":"1332–1357","1334–Female":"1334–Kuollut","1257–Male":"1257–Kuollut","1283–Female":"1283–Kuollut","1303":"1303","1357":"1357","1257":"1257","1334":"1334","ABT    1330":"noin 1330","133